HEADWORD: Labellum
<hw>La*bel"lum</hw> <pr>(l⟦adot⟧*b⟦ecr⟧l"l⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L. <plw>Labella</plw>
<pr>(l⟦adot⟧*b⟦ecr⟧l"l⟦adot⟧)</pr>, E. <plw>Labellums</plw>
<pr>(l⟦adot⟧*b⟦ecr⟧l"l⟦ucr⟧mz)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., dim. of
<ets>labrum</ets> lip.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
lower or apparently anterior petal of an orchidaceous flower, often of a
very curious shape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small appendage beneath the
upper lip or labrum of certain insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Labent</ent>⟦br⟧
